\title{From Objective Reduction to Cascade Crystallisation:\\
A Geometric Closure Model of State Selection}
\author{Lee Smart\\Institute of Vibrational Field Dynamics}
\date{2026-05}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

\begin{abstract}
We propose a single named mechanism for state selection across passive
response, active selection, cognitive substrate, spectral mass projection,
and number-theoretic / PDE / complexity-theoretic / geometric
classes of problem: \emph{cascade closure}. When a field state cannot
maintain coherent projection across a stratified hierarchy of geometric
closure layers, the unresolved mismatch propagates through the
hierarchy until a closure-compatible attractor geometry is selected.
\emph{Collapse} is the external view of this resolution event;
\emph{crystallisation} is the internal view; \emph{cascade} is the
propagation process. We formalise the triad as a rung-indexed
closure-residual functional with an explicit projection stack, position
the binary icosahedral substrate $V_{600}$ and its Laplacian spectrum
as the load-bearing geometric carrier, and identify Penrose Objective
Reduction as a neighbouring geometry-collapse model that the framework
generalises rather than refutes. We document an observer-process
implementation in which the same mechanism realises the seven-component
tuple $\Ocal = \langle B, S, M, G, I, C, A\rangle$ across biological
and computational substrates, and we position the seven Millennium-class
problems as projection-class instances of cascade closure under named
hypotheses, without re-deriving any of their proofs.

This is a consolidation and framing paper, not a new-results paper.
Its mathematical content is largely imported from existing repository
sources at sharply scoped epistemic flags (Theorem, Proposition,
Hypothesis, Conjecture, Interpretive Claim). Load-bearing empirical
claims are either tied to a local re-runnable check or explicitly
marked as source-paper / upstream-repository witnesses; the
companion field-signature audit
(Appendix~\ref{app:field-signature-audit}) records which is which.
\end{abstract}

