\subsection{ARIA runtime mapping}\label{ssec:runtime-map}

The observer-process tuple of Definition~\ref{def:observer-process}
is realised by ARIA across two source tiers. Tier~1 is the in-repo
reproducibility bundle at
\texttt{release-bundle/closure-kernel-papers/papers/aria-chess/repro/kernel/},
which contains six modules; Table~\ref{tab:runtime-map} cites the
five used by the witness map below. The sixth,
\texttt{consciousness\_binding.py}, is a runtime dependency of
\texttt{self\_model\_stream.py} (imported at runtime to supply binding
telemetry such as $\Phi$ and ignition diagnostics) but is not used
here as an independent $\Ocal$ component; the load-bearing realisation
of $\Ocal$ flows through the five modules in the table. The bundle is sufficient for
the kernel-level numerical reproductions in \cite{AriaClosureKernel}
and the substrate-witness slice of \cite{SmartARIAChess}. Tier~2 is
the upstream production runtime cited as
\texttt{ariaChessRepo}~\cite{ariaChessRepo}, which contains the full
production observer-process architecture realised
across boundary sampling, state integration, memory, governance,
closure, action, and replay. The runtime mapping below is audited
2026-05-02 against both tiers; the eventual publication should cite
the upstream repository for any module not present in the in-repo
bundle, in the same pattern that \cite{SmartARIAChess} adopts.

