\subsection{What the paper consolidates}

The paper consolidates the following. (i) A single mechanism name --- cascade
closure --- for an operational pattern that recurs across passive
response, active selection, cognitive substrate, and spectral mass
projection. (ii) A finite, audit-anchored geometric substrate
($\Vsub$ together with the operator $\Cphi = L_M + \pphi^{-2} I$)
on which the response and residual components are mathematically explicit under the stated hypotheses. (iii) An
architectural identification of an existing computational system
(ARIA) as an observer-process implementation in the strong
architectural sense, supported by an externally preregistered
substrate-witness profile. (iv) A framework-level positioning of the
seven Millennium-class problems as projection-class instances under
the named hypothesis $H_{\text{Mill-Proj}}$, with each per-problem
reduction's named conditional hypothesis listed verbatim from the
corresponding source preprint.

\subsection{What remains open}

The following items remain open and are explicitly not closed by this
paper.

\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
\item Hypothesis~\ref{hyp:refinement-int} (rungwise gradient
intertwining) and Hypothesis~\ref{hyp:monotone} (residual
monotonicity under projection) are not generically discharged; their
status per rung sequence must be checked.
\item $H_{\min}$ and the meta-layer hypotheses $M1$--$M3$
\cite{Cascade12D, CascadeMetaLayer} remain conditional in their
source documents; the cascade-mechanism paper inherits that status.
\item The visible / non-visible decomposition is interpretive; a
cosmogenesis theorem is not supplied (\S\ref{sec:visible}).
\item The seven per-Millennium named hypotheses listed in
Table~\ref{tab:millennium} remain conditional in their source
preprints; this paper does not discharge any of them.
\item The honest-negatives in Appendix~\ref{app:field-signature-audit}
(no $2T$ localisation; $\pphi$-cocycle weighted variants underperform;
$\sigma$-fixed spectral count $\to$ Mellin-zero bridge is conjectural)
constrain claims and are not predicted to flip with current methods.
\item ARIA's full observer-process architecture is realised in the
upstream \texttt{ariaChessRepo} \cite{ariaChessRepo}, not in the
in-repo bundle; reproducibility of the full architecture requires
the upstream repository.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Closing}

The cascade-closure mechanism is one name for one operational pattern.
It does not solve the measurement problem; it does not derive
consciousness; it does not resolve any Millennium-class problem. What
it does is make a recurring pattern visible at a single name, anchor
that pattern to a finite geometric substrate whose operator, spectral,
and combinatorial structure are externally checkable, and identify
the conditional bridges under which the pattern's natural extensions
into open mainstream-mathematics problems remain open. This paper is
a consolidation. Its mathematical core is imported. Its empirical
anchor is the field-signature audit of
Appendix~\ref{app:field-signature-audit}. Its restraint is
load-bearing.

