\section{Field-signature audit (re-runnable empirical anchor)}\label{app:field-signature-audit}

This appendix reproduces \texttt{papers/cascade-mechanism/FIELD\_SIGNATURE\_AUDIT.md},
re-run 2026-05-02. Every load-bearing empirical claim in the main text
points back to a row of this table.

\subsection*{Verdict: GO}

The local re-runnable checks (entries A--E below) passed at the precision
claimed by their source papers. Source-paper / upstream-repository
witnesses (entry F) remain separately marked as such. The data also
surfaced three honest-negatives that constrain the paper's scope.

\subsection*{A. \texorpdfstring{$\sigma$}{sigma}-attractor spectrum (RH / Millennium scaffolding)}
Script: \texttt{papers/cascade-derivation/scripts/test\_sigma\_attractor\_spectrum.py}.
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
\item Q1 $\sigma$-fixed fraction $94/120 = 78.3\%$; target $\geq 50\%$.
  \textbf{PASS.} Eigenvalues $\{9, 12, 14, 15\}$ are integer
  ($\sigma$-fixed); the four irrational eigenvalues in $\Q(\sqrt{5})$
  are $\sigma$-paired.
\item Q2 2T-localisation $0.200$ vs baseline $0.200$ (target
  $\geq 1.5\times$). \textbf{HONEST-NEGATIVE.} $\sigma$-fixed eigvecs do
  not preferentially localise on the binary tetrahedral subgroup $2T$.
\item Sim verdict text: ``conversion to a critical-line Mellin-shadow
  zero claim requires the additional spectral-mode $\to$ Mellin-zero
  correspondence (Conjecture \texttt{conj:spec\_to\_zero} in
  rh-formal), which is not established by this script.''
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{B. Mass-spectrum chain forward derivations}
Script: \texttt{papers/paper-v/scripts/run\_chain\_forward\_derivations\_v2.py}.
9 of 9 multiplicative chain coefficients (Z, charm, W, down, bottom,
Higgs, muon, tau, strange) match claimed values exactly under
\texttt{Fraction} arithmetic, derived from $V_{600}$ primitives
$\{\lambda_3, \lambda_4, \lambda_5, \lambda_7, V_0, \dots, V_5,
R_I, R_D(2), R_D(3), R_D(4)\}$. Plus structural EM-splitting
reclassification of neutron via forward-traceable $\alpha$
correspondence.

\subsection*{C. YM Build B\_YM\_P8 --- \texorpdfstring{$\Der(\OO)$}{Der(O)} and stabiliser}
Script: \texttt{papers/millennium-ym/scripts/verify\_der\_O\_su3\_stabilizer.py}.
$\dim \Der(\OO) = 14$ ($\mathfrak{g}_2$, classical Schafer-Jacobson)
and $\dim \stab_{\Der(\OO)}(e_1) = 8$ ($\mathfrak{su}(3)$, classical)
verified at exact rational precision with no prior assumption of
$\mathfrak{g}_2$ / $\mathfrak{su}(3)$.

\subsection*{D. Pentagonal-clock B5/B6}
Script: \texttt{papers/cascade-derivation/scripts/derive\_pentagonal\_clock\_B5\_B6.py}.
Order-10 class canonical $\tau^5 = -1$. Left-mult clock $T_\tau$
decomposes $2I$ into 12 cycles of length 10. $\Fix(T^n) = \emptyset$
for $1 \leq n < 10$; $\Fix(T^{10}) = 2I$. Unweighted Artin--Mazur
zeta $\zeta_T(z) = (1 - z^{10})^{-12}$.

\subsection*{E. Closure kernel passive-regime witness}
Script: \texttt{papers/aria-closure-kernel/repro/verify\_kernel.py}.
Shell sizes $[1, 12, 20, 12, 30, 12, 20, 12, 1]$ exact;
$\|\Cphi^{-1}\| = 2.618034 = \pphi^2$ to machine precision; per-vertex
correlation uniform across all 120 vertices (max $-$ min $= 2 \times
10^{-15}$). \textbf{HONEST-NEGATIVE:} UNWEIGHTED variant wins at
per-vertex correlation $0.976$ vs PHI\_GEOMETRIC $0.888$ and
PHI\_ARITHMETIC $0.884$. $\pphi$-cocycle weighted variants lose; do
not claim weighted-substrate selection.

\subsection*{F. ARIA observer-process witness}
Source: \texttt{papers/aria-chess-paper/paper/main.tex}.
$18/18$ preregistered cortical correspondences hold at unchanged
thresholds. Six drug/sleep EEG signatures pass on a single deterministic
recurrent-layer trajectory at seed $42$. HCP brain functional
connectivity degree-homogeneity (degree standard-deviation) places
ARIA at $-11.58\sigma$ vs HCP baseline; the clustering-coefficient
comparison is a separate $+6.80\sigma$ result and should not be
conflated with the homogeneity figure.

\subsection*{Honest-negatives the paper respects}
\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=*]
\item $\sigma$-fixed eigvecs do not localise on $2T$. The 78.3\%
  $\sigma$-fixed split is the only spectral RH witness; no $2T$
  concentration claim allowed.
\item $\pphi$-cocycle weighted kernel variants lose to UNWEIGHTED.
  Use $\Cphi = L + \pphi^{-2} I$ only.
\item Spectral-mode $\to$ Mellin-zero is conjectural
  (\texttt{conj:spec\_to\_zero}). RH-related claims stay under
  $H_{\sigma\text{-fix}}$.
\end{enumerate}

